[the newsroom] researching: "Why did dirigibles lose to airplanes?"

[router - cheap] triage: broad 'why did X lose' question -> 6 independent angles, in parallel
[editor - reasoning] decompose into independent angles:
    1. safety & public trust
    2. speed
    3. cost & infrastructure
    4. weather fragility
    5. military obsolescence
    6. regulation / were they banned?
[reporter - instruct] 6 reporters running IN PARALLEL, each its own notebook (isolated context):
    safety & public trust      -> "The 1937 Hindenburg disaster destroyed p"
    speed                      -> "Airplanes were nearly twice as fast as a"
    cost & infrastructure      -> "Airships were vast and costly to build, "
    weather fragility          -> "Rigid airships were fragile and repeated"
    military obsolescence      -> "By WWII, aircraft and radar had erased t"
    regulation / were they ban -> "A 1938 international treaty outlawed air"
[checker - reasoning] refute each claim against the wire; keep only what a source supports:
    safety & public trust        sources s1             -> KEEP
    speed                        sources s2             -> KEEP
    cost & infrastructure        sources s3,s6          -> KEEP
    weather fragility            sources s4             -> KEEP
    military obsolescence        sources s5             -> KEEP
    regulation / were they banne (no source)            -> DROP
[copy desk - instruct] citations attached; editor synthesizes the final report.

=== the cited report ===
Dirigibles lost to airplanes for several converging reasons.  The 1937 Hindenburg disaster destroyed public confidence in airships [s1].  Airplanes were nearly twice as fast as airships [s2].  Airships were vast and costly to build, house, and crew [s3][s6].  Rigid airships were fragile and repeatedly lost to storms [s4].  By WWII, aircraft and radar had erased the airship's niche [s5].

=== why multi-agent, here ===
  PARALLELISM  6 reporters worked at once, not one after another.
  ISOLATION    each had its own window -> no interference; more effective context than one agent.
  VERIFICATION the fact-checker dropped 1 unsupported claim a lone agent might have kept.
  SPECIALIZATION reasoning model to plan + check, instruct to report, a cheap model to triage.
  THE TRADE    ~+90% on research evals, at ~15x the tokens - worth it here, not for everything.
  THE LIMIT    it only works because the angles are INDEPENDENT; share state (e.g. coding) and it misaligns.
